  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: normal;&quot;&gt;In the absence of the required Flood Risk Assessment, occupier safety information and sustainable drainage measures, the high risk of un-mitigated surface water flooding in this critical drainage area, including creating additional offsite issues, is considered unacceptable and contrary to National Planning Policy Framework (2023), Policy DM9 of the DM1 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013); Policies CN3 and CN4 of Harrow’s Emerging Local Plan (2024);&amp;nbsp; and Policy SI12 of London Plan (2023).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed rear extension together with the external raised rear patio, by reason of its substantial depth and height above natural ground level, siting and lack of sufficient boundary screening with no.6 Holmwood Close, giving rise to actual and perceived overlooking, loss of privacy and an unacceptable sense of enclosure resulting in poor outlook to neighbouring properites, all of which is contrary to the Policy DM1 of Harrow’s Development Management Policies Local Plan document (2013); Policy GR1 of Harrow’s Emerging Local Plan (2024); and Harrow’s Residential Design Guide SPD (2010).&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
